	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=195158><span id=Sage>DuadilDarquenight</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>123 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>well<br>they pretty much covered it all :P<br>I am by no means a rich warrior, back then or now<br>but I did try to keep my skills maxed or close<br>and for most of the time, I wasn't using the best or even really good weapons<br>there are a lot of cheap weapons available that will help to further all types of weapon skills<br>(all prices are approximate E-Marr prices)<br>bed leg club - 1hb (really good for amazingly cheap) 75pp<br>crystalline spider fang - piercing 100pp<br>Sarnak Battlehammer - 2hb 60pp<br>weighty polearm - 2hs 70pp<br>I am actually using a shimmering partisan (1hand piercing) right now in my offhand and they go for about 200pp or so on E-Marr<br>there are a lot of different weapons that are usable<br>granted they are not the best; nowhere close<br>but they do their job and have served me well<br>sure you can buy armor, but at the prices some of those weapons go for, you're probably better off getting the weapons<br>like yosa and xaanru said, there are some awesome higher level weapons available (wish GSoT was only 2k on my server :P) and it is a major pain to try and catch a melee skill up to max from scratch at a higher level, especially when the mobs you fight are stronger<br>I say keep them up because it really isn't an incovenience and it IS fun to play around with different weapons</p>&nbsp;<br>Duadil Darqueknight<br>Half-Elf Warrior of the 50th Season<br>Order of Mithaniel Marr<br>Erollisi Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474850&alt=0" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474850&alt=0</a></td></td></tr>
