	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1657 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.88]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Pick a weapon set you like. As yosa suggests, using a pair that are two DIFFERENT types will keep two skills maxxed.<br><br>Then just keep around some crappy weapons of the other types. Use them just long enough per level to get your 5 skillups, and rebag them. Or an alternative some people like, when LFG, ask another group if you can pound on their mobs to practice skill.<br><br>I kept my warrior's pierce skill up using velium daggers for quite a few levels, before I got better. Sarnak battlehammer for 2hb (paid 40pp, 30 dmg, 40 dly) and used a lammy jade mace combo as my regualr weapons, up til 35, when I swapped lammy for veno axe for the proc.<br><br>A good example of why to keep them all maxxed is the greatsaff of thunder. At one time, 2hb was considered a joke for warriors, as there were few good aggro weapons. Now the greastaff of thunder comes along, and outdamages AND outtaunts a lot of the traditional warrior weapon combos, like frostbringer/wavecrasher. On my server, GSOT is selling for under 2k. Not something you would want to pass on, just because 2hb skill is low right?<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Aug 20 10:17:43 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
